Package: Rbebelm
Title: 'R' Bindings for 'BebeLM' 'CPU' Inference
Version: 0.2.0-0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Sounkou Mahamane", family = "Toure",
           email = "sounkoutoure@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Maxime", "Chevalier-Boisvert", role = "cph",
           comment = "BebeLM upstream"),
    person("Hiroaki", "Yutani", role = "cph",
           comment = "savvy R/Rust interface")
  )
Description: Provides experimental 'R' bindings for the pure-Rust 'BebeLM' 'CPU'-only language-model inference library <https://github.com/maximecb/bebelm>. The native layer is structured as runtime-selected Rust backends so portable 'R' binaries can avoid build-host-specific SIMD assumptions while still using optimized backends when available.
